Heart-wrenching impacts of an EF4 tornado packing 170 mph winds, carving a 60 mile path of destruction through central #Mississippi — this storm had a pedigree after dropping 2 rare tornadoes in California earlier in the week, so I guess it’s not surprising my cross-country trek ended so horrifically.  Too many lives lost, and entire towns demolished. Witnessing the response of help from neighboring communities was inspiring and hope giving. Kudos to my California crew and the unflappable #Dallas team @ohshoot_itsjuan @scholjam — our hearts, thoughts, and prayers are with the victims — if you want to help, charity navigator is a good resource 🙏 https://www.charitynavigator.org/discover-charities/where-to-give/mississippi-tornado/

This month marks the start of my 10th year with ABC News, and I couldn’t be more pumped to continue this journey with all of you.  I always dreamed of working for this network as a kid, and my children are equally psyched that I will now be home most weekends!  I'll continue doing what I’m doing, contributing across all ABC shows and platforms Mon-Fri, while getting more quality time with my kiddos on the weekends :)
My thanks to the bosses who listened and made this work-life balance possible.  I’m also grateful for an exciting new project with NatGeo that has me exploring some very very cool stuff… more to come!
